  "prompt": "How can I improve my IELTS writing skills?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to improve your IELTS writing skills:\n\n1. Understand the Test Format\n- Familiarize yourself with Task 1 and Task 2 requirements\n- Learn the time management for each task\n\n2. Practice Regularly\n- Write essays and reports under timed conditions\n- Use official IELTS writing practice materials\n- Get feedback from teachers or native speakers\n\n3. Vocabulary and Grammar\n- Expand academic vocabulary\n- Learn complex grammatical structures\n- Practice using varied sentence structures\n\n4. Task Response\n- Always address the full question\n- Develop clear and coherent arguments\n- Use specific examples and evidence\n\n5. Structure and Coherence\n- Learn proper essay and report structures\n- Use linking words and transitions\n- Organize ideas logically\n\n6. Time Management\n- Practice writing within 60 minutes\n- Allocate time for planning, writing, and reviewing\n- Learn to quickly outline your essay\n\n7. Learn Common Mistakes\n- Study common IELTS writing errors\n- Practice self-correction techniques\n\n8. Reading and Exposure\n- Read academic texts and articles\n- Follow writing blogs and resources\n- Study band 8-9 sample essays\n\n9. Use Online Resources\n- IELTS preparation websites\n- YouTube tutorials\n- Writing correction services",
